4.5.5.    Security


          The train shall be designed to meet the following security requirements:


    (a)   Limit the ability to place or hide explosives on or under vehicle;
    (b)   Improve the ability to see into and out of vehicle;
    (c)   Reduce the damage that would result from an explosion;
    (d)   Reduce the damage that would result from a fire;
    (e)   Reduce the damage that would result from contaminants;
    (f)   Enhance emergency egress through doors;
    (g)   Protect the train operator from physical threat;
    (h)   Network the vehicle with the TCC;
    (i)   Enable communications between the train operator and passengers; and
    (j)   Secure the vehicle from theft/unauthorized operations.


          Guidelines according to the “Transit Security Design Considerations” issued
          by the U.S. Department of Transportation (document ref: FTA-TRI-MA-26
          7085-05, issue date: November 2004) shall be followed where applicable.

