( 1 ) Within equipment, conditioned electrical power shall be DC-isolated from
      chassis and structure except at a single point;


( 2 ) Within equipment, the single-point reference shall be routed external to the
      equipment for termination to ground, or routed directly to the chassis for
      termination;


( 3 ) The control power bus return shall be independent of the primary electrical
      power return and shall be referenced to the return system at a single point;


( 4 ) Secondary and tertiary electrical power shall be single-point grounded and
      shall be returned to that single reference ground point;


( 5 ) When all single-point grounds are not terminated to chassis or structure,
      secondary and tertiary electrical power shall be DC isolated by a minimum of
      1 megohm;


( 6 ) Power conversion performed to supply conditioned power to several devices
      or functions shall reestablish a single-point ground reference for the serviced
      equipment or functions;


( 7 ) Equipment shall not depend on other equipment for reference or grounding,
      either signal or power, unless it is also dependent upon the other equipment
      for its power;


( 8 ) Signal circuits with frequencies below 2 MHz, with interfaces external to
      equipment, shall be balanced and isolated from chassis;


( 9 ) All returns and references shall be brought out of equipment on individual
      connector pins;


(10)     Shield connections shall be made to connector shells or to connector pins
       that are, or will be, grounded when mated;

