21.2.5.   The SEM as a process shall place equal emphasis on system capability,
          manufacturing processes, test processes and support processes in the context
          of Specialty Engineering.


21.2.6.   Specialty Engineering


   (a)    The objective of the Specialty Engineering shall be of twofold:
   (i)    to integrate specific system attributes and disciplines into the acquisition
          process; and
   (ii)   to assess and confirm the following system attributes of Specialty Engineering:
   (1)     System Assurance (refer to PS 21.4);
   ( 2 ) Operability Engineering (refer to PS 21.5);
   ( 3 ) Weight Management (refer to PS 21.6);
   ( 4 ) Electromagnetic Compatibility (refer to PS 21.7);
   ( 5 ) Noise Engineering (refer to PS 21.8);
   ( 6 ) Software Management (refer to PS 21.9);

( 7 ) Fire Engineering (refer to PS 21.10).


